{"id":14880930,"mediaExerciseId":"61ebd1c4-7236-47d7-8e09-fb909c9c9023","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612300,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":183,"solutions":[{"id":5958825,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will discuss whether the Tri-State Megabucks regarding the lottery claim options offer is deceptive or not.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/984cd46079b0c428446ba50214a4e97b/7987b7eb48201bbad6a7648548fb1654/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/984cd46079b0c428446ba50214a4e97b/7987b7eb48201bbad6a7648548fb1654/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Tri-State Megabucks presents two options of claiming the lottery win to the participant. The first option was a lump sum of $250,000, and the other is a $500,000 to be received at equal installment for 25 years.\n\nIn general, money's worth today will not be the same value in the future due to constant inflation. Tri-State Megabucks advertisement of the second option is done deceptively; if the participant failed to consider inflation, it might look like the second option is the preferable choice. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":254,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/984cd46079b0c428446ba50214a4e97b/40d3f4b8b9222b77f6b1a1b7aa2cfb39/lateximg_large.png","width":1039},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/984cd46079b0c428446ba50214a4e97b/40d3f4b8b9222b77f6b1a1b7aa2cfb39/lateximg.png","width":520}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To conclude, Tri-State Megabucks advertisement is deceptive as it takes advantage of the inflation factor.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/984cd46079b0c428446ba50214a4e97b/857db9b1be14d5c1bff87bbc3a776b68/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/984cd46079b0c428446ba50214a4e97b/857db9b1be14d5c1bff87bbc3a776b68/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"8e1583b5-42d9-4574-8686-bcebdf23c4b4","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3},{"id":6359328,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We need to determine whether the lottery-offered option is deceptive or not.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Lottery's offer goes like this:\n\n1. $500,000 over 25 years;\n2. $250,000 immediately.\n\nIn this case, generated payment for annuity is $20,000. At interest rate of 6.24% (as precalculated) after 25 years will annuity equal to the lump amount.  ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Interest rate of 6.24% is rather small, so in this case the morality is starting to lean towards blacker. Therefore, the deceptiveness lies in interest rate and splitting amount.\n\nIf the net sum is split into greater chunks or offers a greater interest rate, annuity is more acceptable. Although, annuity is a better option due to taxes and societal problems receiving too much money too suddenly offers.\n\nIn general, the given practice is **somewhat deceptive** as the paid amount was counted under lower interest rate (as stated above), but then again, that is still a large amount won on pure luck, as well as being a large amount in the first place, so morality does balance out somewhat, but scales are still tipped in favor of whoever pays the winnings.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"e8c87ddf-ab5a-4bc7-8000-b2baf275715f","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880931,"exerciseName":"5","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ca7d3622-cd47-41b9-a519-e90b0a98c26c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-5-ca7d3622-cd47-41b9-a519-e90b0a98c26c"},{"id":14880932,"exerciseName":"6","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"4f96ab77-01b8-4d81-b304-2fcf751e9cb1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-6-4f96ab77-01b8-4d81-b304-2fcf751e9cb1"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880929,"exerciseName":"3","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ca7d5541-c02b-421c-883a-c6b32647fe3d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-3-ca7d5541-c02b-421c-883a-c6b32647fe3d"},{"id":14880928,"exerciseName":"2","page":182,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"19be1739-a64e-413d-9959-6ae2dd36e0bd","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-2-19be1739-a64e-413d-9959-6ae2dd36e0bd"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-4-61ebd1c4-7236-47d7-8e09-fb909c9c9023"}